Chinese cooking encompasses eight major regional traditions — Cantonese, Sichuan, Hunan, Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Fujian, Anhui, and Shandong — each with distinct flavour profiles, ingredients, and techniques.  Wok hei (breath of the wok), the smoky char from a screaming-hot wok, is a defining characteristic of many stir-fried dishes.
